1. *Pati* od glavobolje već tri dana. (Suffers from a headache for three days already.)
2. Niko ne želi da *pati*. (Nobody wants to suffer.)
3. On *pati* zbog gubitka voljene osobe. (He is suffering due to the loss of a loved one.)
4. *Pati* zbog svog ponosa. (Suffers due to his pride.)
5. Ona *pati* zbog nedostatka samopouzdanja. (She suffers due to lack of self-confidence.)
6. Njihova ljubav je *patila* tokom vremena. (Their love has suffered over time.)
7. Ovaj problem *pati* već dugo vremena. (This problem has been suffering for a long time.)
8. Iako *pati*, on se ne žali. (Although he suffers, he doesn't complain.)
9. Njeni roditelji *pate* zbog njenog lošeg izbora partnera. (Her parents suffer due to her bad choice of partner.)
10. Kada patite, morate se boriti da se oporavite. (When you suffer, you have to fight to recover.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "pati" can be translated as "suffers" or "to suffer" in English.